King's College London Mathematics School is a free school sixth form located in the Lambeth area of the London Borough of Lambeth, England.
Established in 2014, the school is sponsored by King's College London and specialises in mathematics. The school is highly selective, with prospective students expected to have GCSE qualifications at grade A or A* in Mathematics and Science as well as five GCSEs in total at grade C or above including English. Prospective students also have to sit an admissions test and attend an interview to gain a place at the school.
The course structure of King's College London Mathematics School requires all students to study A-levels in Mathematics, Further Mathematics and Physics. Students also must choose between an AS-level in either Computing or Economics in their first year, with all students completing an Extended Project Qualification during their second year.
